    id: "ch-11", number: 11, title: "The Whisperer", minutes: 4, status: "Editing",
    paragraphs: [
      "The sun was already beginning to sink when Cyrus arrived at the edge of the yellow forest.",
      "The sky burned in orange and deep gold, stretching long shadows across the trees as if the world itself was being pulled thin at the edges. He stepped down from the carriage. The forest was quieter than he had expected—no birds, no wind, only the dry crunch of leaves beneath his boots.",
      "He held his torch tightly as the darkness gathered around him.",
      "Hours passed. By the time the night arrived fully, the forest had become a void of shifting shadows. He stopped.",
      "Before him was an opening in the earth—exactly as Bruce's diary had described. The same jagged stone mouth. The same darkness beyond it.",
      "\"So it wasn't fiction,\" he murmured.",
      "He stepped inside.",
      "The air changed immediately—heavier, damp, cold. The flame shuddered against stone walls covered in faint scratches and old markings whose meaning he could not read.",
      "Then he heard it.",
      "Breathing.",
      "He raised the torch.",
      "In the deepest part of the cave, a figure knelt in the dark. A man—scrawny, barely clothed. He was prostrating. Again and again, his forehead meeting the stone floor in a rhythm that suggested ritual, not voluntary movement.",
      "\"Hey.\"",
      "Cyrus took a cautious step forward. The man did not respond. Only continued bowing.",
      "He moved closer. \"Hello?\"",
      "The man stopped.",
      "Slowly, he turned his head.",
      "Their eyes met, and Cyrus froze.",
      "The man's face was caked in dirt, his hair matted into a wild beard, but even so—Cyrus knew him. Not from this timeline. From a future that was quickly dissolving. From a name in a worn brown notebook.",
      "\"…Bruce?\"",
      "Silence.",
      "Bruce's eyes widened slightly, as though recognizing something familiar that was just beyond his reach. Then his lips trembled.",
      "He spoke.",
      "It was not a language Cyrus understood. But in his mind, the words translated themselves with a clarity that had no business existing.",
      "\"Thank the Lord of Secrets for bestowing me such tender feast.\"",
      "Cyrus took a step back. \"What are you saying?\"",
      "Bruce's expression twisted. He rose from the floor. Drool ran down his chin. His eyes were no longer recognizably human.",
      "\"Hey—Bruce, stop!\"",
      "Cyrus reached into his coat and pulled out his knife. But Bruce moved faster. His mouth opened and the same incomprehensible tongue broke from him again.",
      "\"Ravage.\"",
      "Pain surged through Cyrus's head—not from the outside, but from within, something deeper and more catastrophic than any physical blow. His vision shook. His thoughts came apart.",
      "\"Ghk—what—\"",
      "The knife dropped. His hands went to his hair. He fell to his knees. \"Stop—!\"",
      "The world felt like it was collapsing inward.",
      "Then a shadow moved—from Cyrus's own shadow, faster than a man had any right to move. A figure emerged as though he had been waiting beneath reality itself. A man in black gloves, the crescent moon symbol on the back of his hand faintly luminous in the torchlight.",
      "The bodyguard.",
      "Before Bruce could close the distance, the shadowed man struck. He grabbed Bruce by the head and drove him into the cave wall with brutal force. Stone cracked.",
      "Bruce staggered. He did not fall. He roared.",
      "Cyrus was still on the ground, clawing at his own scalp, the pain in his mind fracturing everything. \"Stop—! Stop—!\"",
      "Above him, the two figures fought. Bruce lunged; the bodyguard drew a gun mid-motion—but Bruce twisted and knocked it free. The weapon clattered across the stone floor and stopped near Cyrus's hand.",
      "\"Cyrus!\" The bodyguard's voice was sharp. \"Pick it up!\"",
      "\"What—\"",
      "\"Shoot him! He's not thinking anymore!\"",
      "Bruce turned. His eyes locked onto Cyrus. Empty. Hollow. He advanced with the steady, unhurried movement of something that had stopped being Bruce a long time ago.",
      "Cyrus's hand found the gun. His whole arm was shaking.",
      "\"No… I told her I would bring him back…\"",
      "Bruce took another step.",
      "\"Shoot him!\"",
      "Cyrus shut his eyes.",
      "\"…I'm sorry.\"",
      "BANG.",
      "Bruce's body jerked backward. Then collapsed.",
      "Silence swallowed the cave. Only the sound of breathing remained.",
      "Cyrus stood frozen over the gun. \"…I killed him.\"",
      "Minutes passed. Neither man moved.",
      "Then Cyrus, slowly, turned toward the wall Bruce had been facing when he entered. He stepped closer and held the torch up.",
      "A carving. A figure etched deep into the stone—a man with a veiled face, eyes closed, hands pressed together in silent prayer. It felt divine. Wrongly sacred. The kind of sacred that had been constructed to serve something that wanted worship more than it deserved it.",
      "And beneath it, a single word carved into the stone:",
      "WHISPERER",
      "\"…What is this.\"",
      "A cold metal touch pressed against the back of his head.",
      "He didn't need to turn around.",
      "\"You've seen something you shouldn't.\"",
      "The bodyguard's voice was calm. Measured. Final.",
      "Cyrus swallowed.",
      "\"…So I was never meant to leave here alive.\"",
      "The torch flickered once. And the cave went silent.",
    ],
